Poured from the can this isn't the best looking brew. Fairly hazy and opaque with plenty of white particles floating around. Aroma is largely pine and citrus driven. Can definitely get a sense of the abv here as it doesn't go unnoticed. That being said it is not overbearing. There is a raw hop character in the aroma as well. Finish is full of pineapple and passion fruit. A really tasty DIPA from VT and a solid brewer. It is worth noting that I scored a couple 4-packs of this and it is incredible how quickly the flavor drops off with age. 568 charactersJimmys, Sep 30, 2016
