4.35/5  rDev -4.6%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.25Remarkably clear for a NE IPA, with a slightly darker honey color as well. Pure white, frothy, creamy head.
Smells like a Lagunitas offering - sweet and tropical, almost cloying, with some pine around the edges.
Big lime, mango and candied orange up front. Melon/watermelon and honey mid palate and more traditional IPA piney bitterness on the rear. Bitter orange hop candy lingers forever on the finish. Really clean flavor profile - nothing muddy about this one. Although towards the end of the pint it begins to resemble a Lagunitas Sucks or Waldo more and more (not necessarily a bad thing).
Incidentally, I tried this next to Heady Topper, and SOS was decidedly more sweet and tropical. Heady had a softer palate of peach, apple and grape (think champagne) and was more muddled than SOS. About equally bitter. 817 charactersMongrel, Jun 25, 2016
