4.93/5  rDev +8.1%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5Poured into a snifter/tulip/wine hybrid glass from a 16.9 oz can
A - Bright orange with a hint of copper, two finger frothy pure white head and some legs/lacing
S - Huge hops, musty funk, dry and sweet grains/malts, English ale yeast, orange,  tropical, grapefruit, citrus rind, sugar, green/brown earth, dank and your lawn the day after it was mowed.
T - Smooth hops up front, very sweet malt/grain with some slightly toastiness mixed in there, peach, mango, pineapple, pine, orange, island flowers, grapefruit, very floral, fresh water, dry yeast, 
M - Full bodied, well balanced, great complexity, medium acidity, medium carbonation with a huge hoppy/malty extravaganza on your taste buds, 
D/O - One of the best IPAs I have ever had. Out of the can or in a glass just a model of perfection. The best quality this beer has is not doing to much but what it does is beautiful. The hops are bright, the malt/grain sexy, Stands with Heady, Elder, Hopslam and the like. Amazing!
Final thoughts - no idea on the price as it was a gift and a perfect 8% ABV. I would recommend drinking thsi one and not hanging on to it. If you find it on tap, drain the keg! 1,159 characterswhatthehull, Jun 05, 2016
