4.41/5  rDev -3.3%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.25Sampling a cool pounder can poured into a snifter. The beer pours a slightly hazed gold to copper color. A fluffy bleached white head foams up  2 cm even with a gentle pour.  The head slowly recedes to a sturdy surface layer that leaves some clingy lattice on the glass after each sip.
Aroma is piney hops, some citrus with lemon and peach and mango.  Quite a complex nose and definitely hop forward.
The first sip reveals a fairly smooth body and fine yet very tingly carbonation. Texture is smooth and the beer is easy to drink. Flavor is a bit of caramel but moves to all hops very quickly after the first swallow moves across my palate.
Grapefruit rind and mango hit my lips and then some pine notes and a very dry astringent aspirin bite on the finish.
No hints of the ABV as I work through the can and I finish it rather quickly after opening and pouring into my glass.
This is an enjoyable beer, and very complex hop character.  While I liked it a lot it may be a victim of the hype train as it didnt completely blow me away. 1,032 characterssulldaddy, Apr 09, 2016
