4.89/5  rDev +7.2%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 5A: Crystal clear gold liquid with a generous tight head.
S: Dear Lord. Bursting with more citrus than I can explain. A nice hint of pine and a little sweet malt.
T: Very bright up front; more resin than on the nose with tons of grapefruit, a hint of apricot and a subtle bit of pureed peach. After an intense beginning it smooths out perfectly into a long resinous finish. A slight breath of ethanol on the way out.
M: After the nice carbonation at the beginning it gets silky smooth. You expect more tongue scrape but there is almost none to finish even with all the piney flavors.
O: This is the second time I've had SoS and it's just as great as I remember. I can't think of a DIPA that is as perfectly balanced and flavorful as this. Amazing. Thanks so much, Joe! 767 charactersRockjocknroll, Mar 12, 2016
