3.88/5  rDev -14.9%look: 5 | smell: 3.25 | taste: 4 | feel: 4 |  overall: 416 oz Can dated 12/29/15 12:04
A — Pours a vibrant orangey hue into the glass, clear initially, but a bit of sediment towards the end of the pour creates a nice slightly hazy orange body of beer in the glass. A smooth off-white colored head forms on top and leaves behind some nice consistent rings of lacing.
S — Smell is nice and citrusy, bit of lemon, hit of orange peel and pith, some light tropical hints of pineapple and mango, little bit of pine on the finish, overall balanced and intriguing.
T — Layers of flavors ranging from bitter citrus to semi-sweet tropical fruits. A lemony start leads way to some pineapple, melon, mango as well, a little bit earthy, resinous, and piney on the finish. A nice hoppy display and showcase in balance.
M — Medium bodied, just the right amount of carbonation, a smooth and lingering bitter finish.
O — Very nice overall, a well done Imperial IPA. Not the best in the world, but still a nice example of the style. 976 charactersMoose90, Mar 06, 2016
