4.68/5  rDev +2.6%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75Worthy of its praise, hazy unfiltered look; aromas of citrus and flowers forward on the nose, to be accompanied by more floral citrus fruit on the tongue. Medium-weight, plush, and softly clean drinking. A real winner. 218 charactersGreywulfken, Feb 15, 2016
4.43/5  rDev -2.9%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.5Finally got around to having one of these after trading for it at the Other Half line in Brooklyn. Heard many good things about this beer and for the most part, they were true. Juicy, bright, and easy to down, the alcohol was so well-hidden that it didn't even feel like there was much in here! 
Great pour to this as the beer had golden apricot hue, massive head, loads of clingy lacing left behind, and a opaque shine that begged to be admired. Lots of tropical fruit and candied sugar in the nose with even more in the taste. Mango, papaya, stone fruit, crystalline sweetness, and a bit of honey were found in the taste as the beer had the mouthfeel of the finest of nectars. Sticky, sweet, and juicy, there was so much going on here that it was hard to find the hops. They were here waaaaayyy in the back as they felt like melon and honeydew rind, coming across quite dry in the midst of a beer that was medium in body and carbonated. The herbal and dank aftertaste only added to the depth of this as the complexity of this beer became more and more apparent as it warmed up.
There was a warming from the booze but never could I taste or feel it, which allowed everything else to shine through much more radiantly. This is one of those beers that's not necessarily at the top of the lists but is near the top on everyone's list and for good reason - it's the standard by which many American Double/Imperial IPA's are measured against and a true sip of sunshine because of the brightness of the flavors here. Wonderful stuff that everyone on here should enjoy at least once! 1,579 charactersJerzDevl2000, Feb 14, 2016
