3.8/5  rDev -16.7%look: 3.25 | smell: 3.75 | taste: 4 | feel: 3.5 |  overall: 3.75The color of this is what you would get if you could filter a mimosa.
Hint of orange rind, sweet tart, and fresh dewy, only slightly dank hops.
Zippy, tangy, a little bitter, but very nice. Total glass of summer--which to me is a shame, simply because it really peeves me how many good IPAs come out mid-Winter.
This is my first time with this legendary beer. Granted, this isn't mind blowing, but it doesn't have to be. In fact, I never realized until now, this beer is the template that so many of my favorite younger breweries are looking at in trying to develop flavor profiles for their bigger crowd pleasers. 617 charactersSabtos, Feb 09, 2016
