4.2/5  rDev -7.9%look: 4.75 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.25Poured into a tulip
Appearance: beautiful orange-golden and wonderfully bright. The head is off-white with excellent 1/4" head retention. 
Aroma: the beer smells great yet is way "underpowered." Rather than an olfactory assault, a moderate nasal inhale in required to get the hops. Some tropical fruit and pine, but, again, light. I pick up a very mild amonia scent. 
Flavor: light sweet malt background, which provides a great canvas for the hops. The hops comes through as light citrus and a small bit of pine. Not as tropical and juicy as I expected. 
Mouthfeel: heavy-medium. At 8% abv this is closer to a light double IPA than a strong IPA. 
Overall: certainly worthwhile, but I don't think it's of the caliber consistent with its hype. I received this beer in trade for La Cumbre Elevated IPA. Drinking the two side by side, I prefer the La Cumbre. This beer is very good, just not as good as many of the equally scored BA rated beers like Bourbon County, Parabola etc. 980 charactersPray_For_Mojo, Jan 23, 2016
