Look: hazy light orange with a head that's impressive in both its size and persistence.
Smell: tangelo candy, very slight hint of grassiness. Generally kind of mild.
Taste: like tropical fruit gummy worms. Super clean, lots of fruit, pretty mild in terms of bitterness and sweetness (but a pretty good balance between the two).
Feel: like melted tropical fruit gummy worms. Seriously, this is one of the chewiest IPAs I've had. Highly drinkable.
