4.75/5  rDev +4.2%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75Four pack found in CT  12-27-2015. Local package store. Was searching out Captain's Daughter, and this was an added bonus. 
Served in a 14 ounce curved goblet at 39F.
Right off the batt, the texture, appearance and lacing on this ale are by far the best i have ever seen. This beer just looks so amazing in the glass. From the bronzish,  slightly translucent, plasma like color coding, to the millimeter of carbonation head. Lawsons mastered this. This ale looks so damn good in the glass. Better than Heady Topper in terms of lacing, texture and color, imo..
Aroma is stone fruits, winter melon, smooth vegetal. The nose is fairly descriptive of the flavor profile. 
Smooth and balanced. This IPA creates the aforementioned attributes to perfection. 
Possibly some steel cut oats for the amazing mouthfeel.. It's perfect either way. 
An absolute amazing 4 pack. 
If you are in NY, CT or RI and have access to this, it's an instabuy. Hopefully my fellow beer advocates don't hoard it for trading, and every average IPA drinker can catch a taste of the real deal. 1,070 characterspinyin, Dec 28, 2015
