4.47/5  rDev -2%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 3 |  overall: 4.5Can from Joe back at Zeebra 2015. Good times man! 
From a can into a snifter
APPEARANCE: Pours a 2_ finger, medium looking, frothy white head with great retention. Clear gamboge  orange with no carbonation evident. Head slowly fades to a slight wisp and leaves some foamy lacing on the top of the glass. A slight wisp and ring remain until the end but leave no real lacing. 
SMELL: Lots of mango, pineapple, lemon notes, some grapefruit and light caramel on the nose. Aromatic for sure. Nice tropical fruit and citrus qualities. Huge and excellent. 
TASTE: Floral and tropical up front with mango, pineapple, then some floral hops at the swallow. Big finish is bitter with floral hops, grapefruit, lots of pineapple and mango with nice tropical fruit lingering on the palate. Really good stuff. 
PALATE: Medium body and medium levels of carbonation. Only semi-creamy on the palate, goes down fine and finishes a bit dry. Some well balanced bitterness lingers. 
OVERALL: This is great stuff and well worth the praise it gets around here. Not overpoweringly bitter but well balanced with heaps of tropical fruit character all over the place. The feel could be creamier for the style, but that's a minor complaint. This one is just as good as the label says, actually, so believe it when you read it. Thanks again Joe! Always good times. 1,340 charactersJeffo, Dec 27, 2015
