This is a boozy hop bomb that might be the true definition of a double IPA. Like the warming sunshine on a crisp autumn day. Full of hop oils and piney, tropical fruit. Beautiful color and aroma.
Update on 02/24/17: Happened upon a 4-pack of cans at my local store. Quite the surprise but makes sense because it recently began distribution in Mass. Dated 02/07/17, so just over two weeks old.
Pours like syrup, slightly hazy, with a minimal head. Nose is all resin, pine, and herbs. Fruitier in the flavor with a dry, resinous finish but also thick and sweet. Flavor and sticky feel linger for a while. Quite good and gets better as it warms. Worth the hype? Sure. But I'm glad I never went out of my way for this. 762 charactersGatch, Dec 17, 2015
