S: Moderate to high aromas of citrusy hops are present in the nose—oranges and lemons seem to stand out in particular—along with hints of tropical fruits.
T: The taste follows the smell, but has even stronger flavors of orange and lemon hops.  There is a light to moderate amount of bitterness. Some tropical fruits become noticeable as the beer warms up.
M: It feels medium-bodied and somewhat crisp on the palate with a moderate amount of carbonation.
O: This IPA is bursting with aromas and flavors of citrusy hops—these really shine through because the malts aren't very noticeable.  It's also not very bitter considering the amount of hops that were used.
