4.35/5  rDev -4.6%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.25Tasting notes from November 11th, 2015
Had on-tap@ Prohibition Pig in Waterbury, VT
Appearance - Served in a 7oz glass, the brew is crystal clear and purely golden in color with a white, half finger head. Good retention, then breaks down to reveal a thin, consistent layer of surface suds. The lacing mostly consists of broken lines and spots here and there.
Smell - Strong, citrusy aroma. Orange and grapefruit with a hint of lemon.
Taste - Follows the nose. Packed with a ton of citrus character. Juicy orange with light grapefruit bitterness. Mango undertone. Malts mostly keep hidden, but do enough to provide a generic, bready sweetness. Mid-taste brings mild lemon and a faint leafy mint character that helps to give the finish a bright, clean and lightly bitter send-off. 
Mouthfeel - Medium-bodied with moderate carbonation. Slick texture lendsGoes down quite easily. 
Overall - A strong IPA with bright, citrusy character and little bitterness, this is certainly worthy of praise. I wish I could have snagged a few cans to get more comfortable with the subtle nuances of this brew, but alas I will have to settle for knowing I was lucky enough to have tried it on tap.
05/16/16 Update: Got two cans in a trade. Just as good as I remember! 1,253 charactersTheSixthRing, Dec 07, 2015
