4.47/5  rDev -2%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Can from psweendogg. Thanks, Patrick!
Canned 10/19. 
A clear light copper with a frothy white head that falls off slowly leaving choppy peaks, this looks great. The nose is awesome. Very West Coast, this is dominated by hops, with pine, grapefruit and tropical fruit. Mild resin is present. Semi ripe peaches and mangoes are noticeable, forming a nose balanced by bitterness and fruitiness. The palate opens bitter, mildly pungent and resiny with a clean, pine like bitterness with citrus oils sweetened with fruit juice. Quite brilliant, really. After all the messy IPAs, this is refreshing. Malt character is mild with a touch of burnt sugar and a little cotton candy. Drying, clean, resiny and bitter, this pungent DIPA makes me happy. Alcohol character is quite well hidden too. 783 charactersDefenCorps, Nov 28, 2015
