4.78/5  rDev +4.8%look: 4 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4.5Can from a trip to VT
A: Golden yellow color with mild hop haze. Bright white foam with long lasting retention. Fine titley nit bubbles.
S: Moderate to high hop aroma with an emphasis on tropical and stone fruit (Mango, peach and pineapple,), Light malt aroma, slightly bready. Neutral clean fermentation character. light evergreen aroma comes through as it warms up. No alcohol detected.
T: Moderately firm bitterness with strong hop flavor - Mango and pineapple in the beginning that leads to an overripe papaya flavor. The malt is low with a slight bready flavor that supports the hops nicely. Balance is on the hops. A slight pine and overripe pineapple finish that comes of very dry. 
M: Moderate carbonation with a mild to medium body and a dry finish. The hop oils cover the tongue and provide a creamy pillowy mouthfeel. Slight alcohol warming, but appropriate for style.
O: Great beer, it reminds me of a bigger version of Zombie Dust with a dryer finish. The only thing that would improve this beer would be a little mellower alcohol presence. 1,058 charactersguityler83, Nov 03, 2015
