4.4/5  rDev -3.5%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.516oz can poured into a globe.
A: Golden-Amber colored with some haze to it. Fine-bubbled white head retains at a full inch in height and leaves chunky rings and patches on the glass.
S: Mango, tangerine, pineapple. Fruit cup. Spicy hops, leafy, soft pine. Whiffs of caramel and light toast. Vibrant and tropical.
T: Mango, cantaloupe, tangerine, pineapple. Earthy, spicy,  tobacco, good dose of pine. Bitterness is stiff and even throughout. Sturdy malt base brings some caramel and honey flavors. Light prick of alcohol. Trailing earthy/pine hop finish.
M: Hefty medium-thick body. Round and sturdy malt texture with a creamy and chewy feel. Slightly coating too. Astringency is gripping. Light alcohol warmth. 
O: Great balance for the style. Intense earthy and tropical hop flavors play off of a more traditional and hefty malt base. It's a classic double IPA for the new age. Perhaps a little more grounded than some of the other highly touted Vermont DIPAs, though every bit as good. 993 charactersryan1788a5, Nov 03, 2015
