4.7/5  rDev +3.1%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75Poured into a Dogfish traditional oversized snifter.  Bottom of can says 09/21/15.
A- Pours a medium amber color with a 3/4 inch off-white head that retains like a champ before slowly lowering to a thick ring around the edge of the glass and a mostly full sheet of surface foam.  Semi-resilient lacing leaves large clots behind.
S- Bright citrusy hop aroma  brings to mind pineapple, apricot and mango.  A bit musty and dank with a slight cat pee essence.  Tiny alcohol presence.
T- Lots of stone fruit flavor including the aforementioned mango and apricot.  The bitterness level is spot-on as well as the alcohol presence making it incredibly drinkable for the ABV.  
M- Perfect amount of sharpness from the hops with medium carbonation and a body leaning toward the lighter side.
O- Definitely gives Heady a run for its money.  While not as piney or earthy as Heady, it's a fantastic DIPA that rides an excellent balance between bitter and fruity. 954 charactersImmortale25, Oct 19, 2015
