4.62/5  rDev +1.3%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.5Description: Slightly cloudy, golden color with a thin white head.  Aroma is complex with a lot going on: citrus, peach, grapefruit, pine, orange, etc., and it all works together very well.  Taste is initially fruity with peach and grapefruit and then slowly drifts into some bitterness at the end.  The bitterness then fades into a very clean, dry finish.  Carbonation is light to medium and the alcohol is well hidden and barely noticeable.
Suggested food pairing: Grilled shrimp
If you like this beer then you should also try: Abner
Ideal time to drink this beer: Sitting in a lounge chair or maybe laying in a hammock somewhere on a dock in the Caribbean.  The sky - and your schedule - are completely clear.  The beer is so delicious that you almost think it'd be worth it to take off and head back to Vermont to get some more of it.  Almost.
Overall: 4.5 (This beer is very good and I would definitely drink it again) In addition to having the Crash Kings song "Mountain Man" on loop in my head ("I'm sipping on some sunshine!")I had high expectations for SoS and it lived up to the hype.  Great balance of fruity and bitter.  I was only able to secure one can which is a shame because it occurred to me while drinking it that I could really go for about a gallon of it.  Super smooth, super drinkable.  If you're an IPA fan, this is one to seek out. 1,360 charactersSHDoyle, Oct 10, 2015
