4.12/5  rDev -9.6%look: 4.25 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4Thanks to angrybabboon for the can.
Appearance: Mostly clear with a slight haze. Dark orange-gold. Head is white, creamy, and fluffy. Drops to a small dense cap with solid retention. Big notches of lacing persist throughout. Moderate carbonation on the pour.
Smell: Hits tropical right up front. Notes of peach and nectarine. Malts are slightly bready with a touch of caramelized sweetness. Slightly roasted. A touch of cracker and biscuit dough as well. Slightly floral and herbal with some solid backing pine branch and a touch of resin. Grapefruit. Light and fruity. Slight hint of alcohol ghosting in the back. Juicy with some minor hints of melon and passionfruit as well.
Taste: Slightly bitter pine layered over a solid tropical push. A good amount of peach and mango with some nectarine rolled in the back. Slightly herbal with a big floral push through the back. Malts are lightly sweet with some solid pale malt. A touch of cracker and toasted white bread. Ever so slightly dank. Herbal. Weed. Some candied hop sweetness. Lingering pithy bitterness sits over the top of the juicy fruit base. A touch of alcohol. Some minor passionfruit and melon as well.
Mouthfeel: Medium leaning ever so slightly to light body with a moderate carbonation. A touch crisp.
Overall: It's solid and incredibly drinkable, but the bitterness rides just a bit high and interferes with the overall enjoyment. Still damn good and worth trying again and again. 1,450 charactersGoblinmunkey7, Sep 20, 2015
