4.21/5  rDev -7.7%look: 4 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.25I bought a 4-pack of this about 10 days ago up in Winooski VT  (for about $14.00 or so). Getting into a 16oz can right now out in The 'Zebo.
Pours a slightly cloudy, medium golden color. Carbo is very minimal and hard to find. The head is a short layer of creamy white bubbles. Doesn't leave a whole lot of lacing, either. Aroma smells like a small bowl of sweet apricot jam with some rindy bitterness thrown in.  It feels pretty smooth on the tongue, and the body is your standard medium.
Flavor has a hint of toasty malt before turning hoppy. There's more apricot-like sweetness and some tangerine. Then things turn more bitter, with some pithy action along with resiny grapefruit. Finishes a bit more on the bitter side than the sweet one. Tasty? Yes, indeed. World-class, sell your firstborn for? Hardly. This is the second can of this I have had since buying it. Wasn't blown away with the first, and now it's confirmed. Another product of the THM™.  Prosit!
