4.59/5  rDev +0.7%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.5Consumed 8/25/15, canned 8/10/15
A: Pours surprisingly clear, medium gold to tangerine in color - pours with a large, white head, fades to a wispy cap, a small collar, and leaves sheets of lacing
S: So hoppy, so juicy, so bright - orange and tangerine juice, with some ruby red grapefruit flesh - floral citrus in abundance - big push of tropical aromas, with juicy pineapple, mango, and maybe some melon - straight up leafy hops, with some resin - an understated herbal element that helps round out the aroma, with some light spice, light mint, and some dank notes - pale malts and pale grains hidden beneath
T: Dangerous - very hoppy, but not in an aggressive, palate-destroying way - fresh-squeezed orange juice, tangerine juice, grapefruit flesh - herbal and leafy hops, with some pine and a light touch of mint - resinous and lightly dank - moderate bitterness - pineapple and mango, with an assortment of tropical flavors - light sweetness with some nice pale malts - extremely, extremely drinkable - hides the 8% ABV well, but I have to admit that there is a touch of alcohol in the finish
M: Medium body, nicely carbonated, smooth, finishes mostly dry, some lingering hop oils
O: False. Liquefied sunshine would melt through my face, thus rendering the act of sipping impossible.
After having this on tap on more than one occasion, I am very happy that I have the opportunity to sit with a can and give a proper review. This stuff is absolutely magical. It is not the best IPA I have ever had, but it is probably in the top 5. It's juicy, complex, and stupidly drinkable. This is worth waiting in line to acquire (which is a big complement coming from me).
Edit: After a couple weeks, this beer falls off a cliff. I'm not adjusting my score, but I think it is important to remember to drink this immediately. 1,823 charactersangrybabboon, Aug 25, 2015
