4.76/5  rDev +4.4%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 5Poured from the can into a Spiegelau IPA glass.
Golden bronze body color, tinged with orange and lemon hues.  Loads of plentiful fine carbonation through the middle.  Frothy rising bleach white head, but also soapy and even bubbled with excellent even pinhead bubbles in the makeup.  Great looking brew.
Excellent aroma.  Mild dank, but a bigger tropical fruity hop note that comes out not so much juicy but almost perfume like.  Fantastic icing sugar like sweetness that just melts and turns to cream and vanilla on the nose, powdery thick and dense, and brings out a pollen floral sweetness even more so.
Palate just sings.  Such a nice controlled icing sugar malt and bittter hop sweetness.  Bright with sweet candy almost Belgian like but far toned down.  Tropical fruit, and floral earthy tones fill the palate.  Mouthfeel is creamy and rich supportive feeling and has an extremely pillow like softness.
Overall.  Just another winner for Vermont IPAs. 960 characterssmakawhat, Aug 08, 2015
