4.58/5  rDev +0.4%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75This one pours a lovely golden yellow with a creamy white head; leaves plenty of attractive lacing on the side of the glass as well. The smell is extremely tropical at first - think shoving your nose into some hybrid of mango and pineapple. There's a little bit of hoppy bitterness mixed with profound dankness in the nose as the beer warms as well. My first taste was slightly less tropical than I was expecting, but is ultimately very consistent with the bright fruity nose. As the beer reaches the back of my throat the tropical fruit flavors segue seamlessly into some a bouquet of hop flavors, before finishing bitter and leaving me wanting another sip almost immediately. 
This one very much lives up to the hype; an astounding IPA. Wish I was able to pick up more than two cans at a time. 796 charactersTomMorris, Jul 30, 2015
