4.15/5  rDev -9%look: 4 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.25appearance- Golden amber and pretty clear.  Pours a two to three inch head.  
aroma- Citrus, pineapple, and floral hops as well as some malty sweetness.
taste- Definitely get the tropical fruits as advertised with pineapple standing out the most along with citrus.  For the malt there's a bit of bread flavor in the middle, but caramel malts mix with resinous hops for a sweet finish that verges on being too sweet.
feel- Medium/full bodied and medium carbonation.  There's a sticky feel to it that's a tad unpleasant, but that's nitpicking.
overall- Great IPA/DIPA, but it just didn't wow me as anticipated.  The hop flavor is very nice with pineapple and citrus and the malt is solid, but too sweet at times. This might be due to the fact that its almost two months old at this point (even though I just bought it at the store), but I don't think that should have affected things too much.  The hop flavors certainly didn't disappoint, but in the end feel was a bit too sticky and the malt a bit too sweet. 1,012 charactersCTbrew32, Jul 24, 2015
