4.93/5  rDev +8.1%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5July 2, 2017. On tap at [name withheld to protect the innocent]. Since my first taste back in '15 this white whale has been on my wish list every Christmas, Birthday & "...no it really was nothing to simply plug your mouse back in to get your computer to work again, but if you insist, I'd love a Lawson's Sip o' the next time you drive through CT"  request list.
But now it's flooded the NYC beerscape, so I sought it out. All I can say is absence does indeed make the heart grow fonder. The cans I rec'd back in March were all on the cusp of the use by but were still very, very good. The draft I had last night was just OK. 
I will reiterate that I'm not the biggest IPA fan in the world...let's just say I'm highly critical of over the top hops, so if you want to go BIG, just keep right on going because you're wasting precious fluids on the likes of me.
I will give this another shot to be sure mis-handling is not the culprit, but to me, this draft version pales in comparison to the cans I've enjoyed. And here I thought I'd found a soulmate in the IPA world. :^(
Mar 2, 2017. From can at home. Just as I remembered.  At risk of offending all the hoppy-go-luck IPA fans, I must say that this is my ideal IPA.  Clean on the palate, bitterness is a characteristic, not the star of the show & a body that conjures images of Scarlett Johansson at her Sci-fi best, (without the CGI overkill). And of course there's the taste.
No matter what anyone says. this stuff tastes great, so great that you no sooner swallow it when your brains saying MORE.
Jul, 19, 2015 At bottle share, Coopers, Chelsea, NYC. I am an un-hoppy guy. That being said, this stuff is spectacular. Among the 8 or so geeks I was sharing with, no one ventured a guess as to what hops or mix made it the taste treat it was. 
Tropical notes all up in your face from the get go.
