4.63/5  rDev +1.5%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75A - Golden orange, hazy transparency, white head forming tight and white, with extensive lacing.
S - Floral notes, with strong catty element, and also a tropical fruit note, mango, with a minty, almost menthol note as well, all of which is fortunately integrated into the total package, making it much more attractive than it sounds.
T - The fruit is front and center, with big mango and peach notes, citrus in the form of tangerine and grapefruit, a touch of pith, and a close that goes more for citrus essence, grapefruit oil and floral notes in a long bitter fade.
M - Given how punchy the taste is, the mouthfeel is supple.  Decent carbonation comes with a solid drying, but the beer keeps from becoming taxing.
O - Huge beer, with big hop flavors, crafted carefully and with a lot of finesse.  Delivers a fruity, full experience that is bright as the name suggests.  A top tier IPA for sure. 900 charactersTsar_Riga, Jul 08, 2015
