4.71/5  rDev +3.3%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75Can; thanks for sharing, Emma!
A: Hazy orange-amber body under a finger of dense ecru head; good retention and sticky lace. Attractive.
S: Decadent hoppiness, redolent of oranges, mangoes, and strawberries at first; some floral and herbal notes in the background keep it from being too sweet. Excellent.
T: Follows the nose precisely, with a delicious and complex array of hop flavors. Tropical fruit up front, citrus in the middle, and cleanly herbal bitterness on the finish. Long, delicately dank aftertaste. 
M: Soft, smooth, and moderately carbonated. Lovely.
O: Splendid beer; it beat out a can of Heady in the evening's side-by-side comparison, but was a narrow loser to the truly spectacular Trillium Vicinity. All top-tier DIPAs to be sure; not sure why this one is listed as a single IPA when it's the same ABV as Heady, but in any case I find that 8% is the sweet spot for balancing maximal hop flavor with maximal drinkability. 
Cheers! 954 characterswoosterbill, Jun 27, 2015
