4.63/5  rDev +1.5%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75People herald this biz as the crème de la crop, I was out in Denver and saw a can of this as a trophy.  I’ve had it before, but after my CO trip let’s see if it’s changed at all.
A:  Pours a clean orange gold with a thick and foamy two finger head, no visible carbonation
S:  Citrus, passion fruit, pineapple, and stone fruit – maybe gooseberries . . . kinda Sav Blanc white winey.
T: The passion fruit and pineapple sweetness come out like cotton candy and it’s pretty awesome; it is a tad busy, but I believe it’s just Citra hops.  It’s got a great sweet orange blossom taste on top of that and it just bursts with fresh fruit sweetness.  Ok Mr. Lawson, you win this one.
M:  It’s a great balance of full body sweetness, carbonation, and hop bite (alcohol too) – just well done.
O:  People love to deflate hyped beers, either because the hype had their expectations set in the heavens or because it makes them feel cool to shoot down/ nonchalantly brush off the coveted, or both.  Either way, it’s not fair; if I had never heard of this beer and picked up a pack, I would be delighted with how good this is.  After hearing that people wait in line or drive for hours to get a pack, my expectation would change or I would cock my head sideways in confusion . . . depends on how far alone in the trying continuum I am in this scenario.  Word play aside, it’s a damn great beer that should be appreciated as the one-man-army-brewing-out-of-a-shed-developing-this-recipe-then-getting-a-large-enough-following-to-score-a-contract-brewing-deal-with-Two-Roads-Brewing-to-mass-produce kinda beer it is, the man who made this beer isn’t too far off home brewer status.  93 1,695 charactersPanda_Brew, Jun 15, 2015
