Overall:  Citrus nose with a balanced hop presence that does not overpower but hits you right away, and stays with you before you finish and after words.   The Captains Daughter I am side by siding against the Sip leaves you with nearly the same hoppy goodness, but is not in your face right away.   I smell more citrus on the Sip as well.    Sip simply has more flavor.   But at a cost if pounding/drinking fast.    Captains Daughter would be easier to drink fast because the hops and citrus is more muted.   If you cant get Sip, then Captains Daughter would be a fantastic second choice in my area. 878 charactersShort-Pour, May 31, 2015
