4.16/5  rDev -8.8%look: 5 | smell: 4 | taste: 4 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4My last of a 4-pack :(
A - I prefer my IPAs filtered; it just makes them look cleaner.  This is clear as could be with a fluffy white head of an inch and a half.  Bubbles are streaming off the bottom of the glass.  Beautiful.
N - Not bitter at all.  Dank, but not bitter.  I get fresh citrus / fruit juice, like orange juice, grapefruit juice, pineapple juice?  Very nice.
T - To me this is like the younger brother of Double Sunshine.  I find that to be extremely spicy, and not at all clean.  The spice is still there on this one, but much more subdued.  Dank, bitter, piney hops round out the flavor.
M - Yeah!  Somehow all of the NE IPAs have this in common; the liquid turns to froth immediately in my mouth, as if I'm not even drinking; it's more like I'm eating cotton candy.  Not too dry on the finish, so I can really sip on it.
O - Definitely a winner. 867 charactersCraftFan5, May 11, 2015
