4.44/5  rDev -2.6%look: 3.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5My first moment tasting the beer occurred in...São Paulo?!? I was shipped a pair of cans which were brought to Fil's apartment, and part of the reward is taking part of tasting it. From a 16 ounce can, on to the beer:
A soapy head with fair retention sits on the top of this glowing electric orange color of a brew. Not to be let down, the aroma comes out with a cornucopia of fruity smells. Out comes cantaloupe, orange, grapefruit, grass, kiwi...nicely done! 
One flaw I could think of is that this beer could have a wee more malt presence. That being said, the performance of those lupulins is outstanding. The beer is quite clean, all sorts of tropical fruit juices from passionfruit to orange keep the palate in a happy mood. Paired with a medium full body and no none of that hop bitterness, I suspect it is similar to a sip of sunshine. 
Excellent beer and worth talking about. 888 charactersDoubleJ, Mar 25, 2015
