4.57/5  rDev +0.2%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Had this on 2015-03-22 and again on 2015-10-30 and 2016-05-25 in Columbia, PA from fresh, 16 oz cans.  Thanks Mike, for turning me on to this fine brew.
A - Mildly hazy, golden-orange with a 2.5-finger pillowy white head, a light touch of sediment and very nice lace.  BTW, the can itself looks really refreshing.
S - Orange, pineapple, honeysuckle, fresh hop buds that are a little dank and very floral.  
T - Fresh, juicy oranges, pineapple, grapefruit, peach and papaya sweetness with a touch of light malt.   The refreshing, outdoorsy flavors of pine and mint compliment the present-but-moderate bitterness delivered by the various hop flavors that ebb and flow on the tongue (and nose).  The aftertaste continues these same flavors;  and remains well balanced; slightly favoring hop bitterness.  
M - Medium body and low-medium carbonation.  Smooth, sticky, creamy, resinous and just lightly prickly.  
O - A great DIPA; nearing the lofty heights of Double Sunshine. 976 charactersTucquan, Mar 22, 2015
