4.99/5  rDev +9.4%look: 4.75 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5Look: Bright, clearly unfiltered. Awesome and appetizing orange tone.
Smell: Honestly, best smelling beer i've ever had. Pine with intense smells of orange, grapefruit, lemon peel. The most appetizing, wake-me-up smelling beer i've ever come across
Taste: Exactly like the nose hops are forward and mingle and dance with the intense citrus notes of grapefruit, orange, lemon, and melon. Quite honestly the best tasting beer i've ever experienced. Very little beers would make me smile like this and ever fewer have a flavor that is pleasant at any time. I can't imagine a scenario where this wouldnt just empirically taste amazing. 
Feel: Just right. Has a sense of thickness you expect from juice but retains the classic 2xIPA lingering mouthfeel. Perfection
Overall: Perfection. Can't think of a beer that does everything that this beer does this well. The hype is warranted and then some. 895 charactersYeahRightt, Mar 19, 2015
