4.92/5  rDev +7.9%look: 5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 5For lack of a more appropriate colloquialism; this beer is the absolute balls. 
The pour is an ever so slightly hazy golden orange color with a nice, fluffy white head. Great retention and some decent lacing. 
The aroma is an orgy of citrus fruits and dank, grassy pungency. There are notes of orange, grapefruit, tangerine, and pineapple. The malt is subtle, but provides a nice, fresh baked bread character. The aroma leans on the sweet side, but there's plenty of grass and even some spicy pepper to keep it from being cloying. 
The taste is unsurprisingly very citrusy, with notes of juicy orange and fresh tangerine. There's also a bit of grapefruit and even some mango. The bitter hops are also very present, and the sweet and bitter notes are basically cuddling in the glass watching Game of Thrones. Like the aroma, the malt is subtle but adds a nice doughy character to the flavor. There's even some caramel sweetness hiding around. 
The feel is medium bodied with medium carbonation. Incredibly creamy and smooth, yet despite the 8% ABV remains crisp and refreshing.
Overall, this beer. This. Beer. Every bit as good as Heady Topper and in some ways perhaps even better. It's incredibly well balanced. It's juicy and sweet, yet bitter and piney. The malt is not a main character but is more like a supporting character that deserves far more recognition and maybe even a Golden Globe nomination. Truly one of the best beers I've ever had. 1,453 charactersScaryEd, Mar 13, 2015
