The pour is a muted orange, lightly carbonated. It’s a bit tough to blow the Fou out of my nose, but this smells just like Halos, minus the easy peeling. All orange, all the time. 
Sip of Sunshine is an apt metaphor for the liquid pouring into my biggest head orifice. Big huge sunshine energy has turned into oranges & mangos, with a backing quartet of sweet candy. Bitterness only arrives mid-palate & is more mildly irate than bitter (although my burps taste awesome), along with a slight herbal quality, touch of dust, orange creamsicle. Nicely resinous, thick in the hips, the mouthfeel might be the pinnacle here. Although I could pound down a few of these. 
