4.84/5  rDev +6.1%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75Poured from a 16oz. can dated 2/13 into a tulip glass.
Appearance: A turbid and hazy golden-yellow with a touch of orange. Huge, billowy white head with lots of small bubbles rising through the beer. Heavy lacing on the glass throughout drinking.
Aroma: So juicy and fresh smelling. Reeks like tropical fruit, with tons of citrus and mango and passionfruit. The can points to a tropical flavor with it's bright yellow color, and the smell matches that. Really inviting and refreshing in the dead of Rhode Island winter.
Taste: One of the most juicy and citrusy IPAs I've ever encountered. Absolutely delicious, and crazy juicy. Only mild bitterness, overwhelmed by layers of fruit and flora aroma.
Feel: Crisp, smooth, and somewhat thick. Drinks wet and juicy but finishes dry and leaves a lingering refreshing feeling in the mouth.
Overall: One of the top IPAs I've ever had; this one can definitely go toe-to-toe with any New England IPA, including Heady Topper. The relatively prevalent availability makes this one a go-to. Fantastic! 1,042 charactersTheElectricOne, Feb 22, 2015
