4.4/5  rDev -3.5%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.25Last of a 4-pack (it went very fast) recently purchased while up in Vermont. Have had this on-tap many times in the past as well. Canned on date is 1-23-15.
A - Tall-boy pours to a big ol snifter hazy orange with a white head. Nice full cap and bits of lace left. Looks good in said big ol snifter.
S - Tangerines, dank, grapefruit, bit of mango, good all-around general tropical grassiness, light sugar cookie malt. Decent strength.
T - Taste steps up a bit with more strength and a bit more complexity. Nice orange/grapefruit/tropical/weedy hop mix with some floral there as well. Sweet and biscuity malt is slight but provides a nice semi-backbone.
M - Smooth, good body, nice swishy medium carbonation, somewhat high bitterness with good malt backing, very solid and quite drinkable.
O - Definitely a very nice DIPA but maybe not quite as remarkable as some other top tier ones coming out nowadays. That being said - really really good. I actually  have had better experiences with this than my few with Double Sunshine. 1,029 charactersChico1985, Feb 06, 2015
