5/5  rDev +9.6%look: 5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5I never want to just hand out all 5's to a beer. I actually look for negatives and things I didn't like as a consumer of the product so I can fairly rate it. This was my first time drinking Sip of Sunshine and I was very impressed. 
It looks wonderful. It has a golden amber hue which is very pleasant. 
The smell is amazing. It's what I expect out of an IPA. I don't want to smell harsh malt in my IPAs. I smell very floral and tropical notes coming through which lets me know what to expect when I taste it. 
The taste is amazing. It's hoppy, tropical, light, slightly bitter, and very drinkable. I'm sure the yeast plays a role in the flavor. It's what I'm looking for. 
The feel is flawless. I can't say anything negative. It's smooth. I don't know how you can rate it any other way. 
Overall this what I'm looking for in an IPA. If you want a malt bomb, then this beer is not for you. If you're not an IPA drinker, I think this beer would turn you onto IPAs. But, you will definitely be spoiled when you try other beers. 
I try to rate on style. IPAs are my favorite style so I am more critical when I approach a new to me IPA. Every beer has subtle differences that each of us like more than others. I just happen to like this style of IPA more than others.  I'm sorry. I couldn't find a flaw with it. Maybe that I don't have more of it! 1,349 charactersDroopy487, Feb 05, 2015
