The pour produces a frothy and creamy head a couple fingers thick. Body is orange and cloudy with trickles carbonation. 4.5
Bright citrusy and floral nose. Piney and resinous below. 4.25
Tasty first sip is mango followed by a malty, somewhat caramel-like flavor with a touch of passionfruit. It's hugely fruity, but then it takes a lemony turn that mingles with sweetness until the finish. 4.5
For a bigger beer, this is smooth and devoid of alcohol. Carbonation is low to medium, the body is medium and almost chewy, with a moderately bitter finish.  4.5
Pretty damn flawless. Juicy and rich, even a month and a half from bottling. 697 charactersONovoMexicano, Jan 05, 2015
