4.74/5  rDev +3.9%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75Thanks to Travis for getting me a bottle of this...and making sure it never left ice from VT.
Just an extraordinary beer. The beer is brilliant, The nose is just fantastic. It is so fresh and floral...so pronounced even after the beer has sat in the glass for a bit. The aromas just burst out of the glass. Probably wrong glass but I recommend snifter...seemed to work for me. It literally explodes with flavor. 
It brings me back to early PTE when it was so fresh and unknown. After so many left on the shelf or boxed and traveled  PTE's It's hard to remember. Definitely like very fresh PTE on tap in No Cal. Literally took me back to DIPA fest at The Bistro in Hayward.
As bottle finishes the beer in glass becomes more creamy and soft. Absolutely spot on, and so unlike most bottled beers.
This is a special beer. As good as it gets. 837 charactersBillRoth, Dec 27, 2014
