3.86/5  rDev -15.4%look: 4 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 3.5 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4TWStandley, Dec 26, 2014
4.35/5  rDev -4.6%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.25Tine802, Dec 26, 2014
4.81/5  rDev +5.5%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.7516oz can dated 7/21/15
L: Very lovely 3-finger off-white head sits on top of a golden brew. Hazy, but not totally opaque. There's some crazy looking lacing here.
S: Heaps of citrus, peach and tropical fruit are just flying out of the glass before I bring my nose in. Definitely one of the most aromatic beers out there. SoS is definitely dry-hopped with loads of Citra. Can't totally verbalize exactly what that aspect is, but I've been having a lot of single-hopped Citra beers lately, and this has all the hallmarks of those hops.
T: This is what an elite beer tastes like. Unbelievably complex. Peaches, mangos, oranges, papaya, and those delightfully sweet yeast esters that are undoubtably Conan or Conan-derived. Again, tons of Citra, especially evident on the finish. It's kind of sweet, but the body is thin enough that it's not overwhelming. To compare it to a more available beer: it's like a more refined Lagunitas Sucks.
F: Only slightly prickly on the tongue, this beer definitely falls into the camp of juicy IPA as opposed to a palate destroyer. Medium bodied, perfect for the flavors. I'm glad there's at least this gentle reminder that it's beer, otherwise I'd think I was drinking some sort of Newman's Own fruit juice. Can't score the mouthfeel any higher than 4.5 though because nothing can compete against Hill Farmstead, especially their Double Citra. But this is very good.
O: The first time I had this, I gave it 5s across the board without a written review. I had it again about a month later and it was clearly a subpar batch with muted flavors and aromas. Today we have again a fantastic example of quintessential Sip of Sunshine. Some beers are undeserving of their hype. This is not one of those beers. Befriend your local beer guy. Ply him with out-of-state rarities. Have him hold you some Sip. You won't regret it. ;) 1,854 charactersOnemoresolo, Dec 26, 2014
