4.75/5  rDev +4.2%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75fosters9, Dec 23, 2014
4.53/5  rDev -0.7%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.522oz bottle, bottles 10/11/14, poured into oversized wine glass
A- pours a clear vibrant golden color with a small creamy and sudsy white head that eventually reduces to a film skimming the top, leaving some short lasting lace behind
S- loads of citrusy hop aroma up front with notes of mango, papaya, passionfruit, grapefruit & orange peel.  Also picking up some floral notes, along with some fresh grass.  Underlying doughy malt with a hint of garlic on the close
T- sharp bittering citrus hop flavors immediately kick in, quickly followed by more citrus flavor of mango, orange zest and passionfruit.  Mid palate consists of fresh grassy flavors with a hint of floral hop as well.  Leafy and earthy, mixed with just a hint of underlying bready malt, dry finish with more tropical hop on the linger
M- medium body with medium carbonation leads to a foamy mouthfeel that continues into a dry finish
O- the intense tropical hop notes are definitely as advertised, as they shine throughout.  Just enough underlying malt to let the hops shine, very good DIPA! 1,062 charactersTreyliff, Dec 23, 2014
