4.75/5  rDev +4.2%Jvrdz24, Dec 16, 2014
4.31/5  rDev -5.5%look: 5 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4.25Beautiful golden pale ale; "sunshine" is a rather apt descriptor. Fairly clear with just a little haze, and topped by a beautiful snow white, light and fluffy head. Very good retention, and huge snowdrift chunks of lace.
Quite a bit in the aroma, but all balanced. The hops are there: juicy, floral, piney, slightly dank, and peppery. The malt is there: sweet and creamy.
Flavor matches. I don't get tons of specifically tropical hop flavors as promised by the description; rather, it's a blend of hop flavors, from dank to resinous to floral to tropical. Quite a noticeable malt backbone, as well, with a diacetyl-like tinge to the flavor.
Creamy yet somewhat lively mouthfeel; a really nice in-between of a slow DIPA sipper and a single IPA gulper. Lasting hop bitterness, with oily retention around an otherwise very slightly dry finish.
There's absolutely no indication this beer clocks in at 8% ABV! There's a heavy, sweet malt presence, but no alcohol presence whatsoever.
This is a tough beer to rate. Some things it does about perfectly (balance, appearance, mouthfeel). Others are very, very good (aroma, flavor) but perhaps not world-class. It's an excellent DIPA, thankfully available in cans. 1,209 charactersRoguer, Dec 16, 2014
4.5/5  rDev -1.3%Jmatt567, Dec 16, 2014
4.63/5  rDev +1.5%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.5Poured from a 22oz bottle (Bottled On Date: 11/13/14) into a 17oz Belgian snifter/tulip glass.
A- A decent amount of sediment at the bottom of the bottle caused me to be careful with the pour.* I was able to yield a slightly hazy (without floaties), beautiful, sunset orange/golden colored beer with a pleasant, 1-finger white, soapy head with great retention. (4.5)
S- A potpourri explodes from the glass: Pineapple, Passionfruit, Mango, Ruby Red Grapefruit, Pine along along with some herbal (almost 'catty') notes and a dose of sweet, biscuty malt. (4.5)
T- The biscuty malt sweetness is perceived, but is quickly railroaded by the tropical juicy goodness delivered from the hops. The hops linger on the palate with a dry, piney finish, leaving you reaching for the glass to grab another sip. (4.75)
M- In conjunction with the massive hop presence, a the lively carbonation helps to lighten the body giving this 8% ABV beer a high drinkability factor. (4.75)
O- Although another great offering from Lawson's Finest Liquids, the ~$10/bottle price tag seems a bit much when you consider other masterful DIPA's like Sixpoint's 'Resin' and 'Bootleg Fireworks' from Baxter Brewing Co. However, Sip Of Sunshine will give the best of Vermont's other DIPA stars a run for their money. (4.5)
* I don't like much sediment in my beer, as I find it clouds all aspects: appearance, aroma and flavor. Therefore I choose to decant as much as I can to deliver me the cleanest beer available (This time, even after employing a mini-snifter to capture the remainder of 'clean' beer, I still ended up losing ~2oz). 1,604 charactersthreeviews, Dec 16, 2014
