Appearance: Nice hazy golden to straw color. Just a slight bit of redness in there as well. Decent head retention on this one as well. Sticks around throughout the drinking of this one. 
Smell: Its a bit absent on aroma, very floral and fruity, but not as dank as some can be in this category. Kind of subtle. But I have had these fool me in the past.
Taste: Wow, this is where they get you. This is a very nicely balanced beer. Not too alcoholic in the flavor for an 8% beer either. Nice resinous hops in there. Citrus fruits, tropical fruits and some earthiness to balance it out. It is not a bit harsh. It is very smooth for a DIPA. I would say that it is in the same category and maybe edges out the Stone Enjoy By. I might have to try the newest iteration to compare them. 
