4.62/5  rDev +1.3%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75SERVING: Bottle
BOTTLED ON: 11-13-2014 (Consumed 11-23)
A:
Pours a hazy golden (with touches of amber in the light) with three gorgeous fingers of luscious pristine white cream.  Airy descent to a solid 1 finger.  Excellent retention; impressive, shifting lacing.  (4.5)
S:
Super fruity.  Juicy aromas of grapefruit, green pineapple, pine, weed, dank sappy hops.  (4.25)
T:
Resinous fruity hop layers.  Papaya, pine, tropical fruits, bready malt way down there.  (4.75)
M:
Coating, peach-fuzz-like feel with a medium body and lingering sticky dryness.  Quenches and unquenches with giving you a rich palate experience overall.  Excellent.  (4.75)
O:
This is definitely among the best IPAs I have ever had.
It is a good all-around package in my mind in that it manages to be very hoppy, very fruity, very bitter, very dry, very creamy, etc. all at seemingly the same time.
Beer pours gorgeous with a excellent head that stays and stays and rings and spots of lacing.  The smell is of pungent hops, the kind where you can feel it in your sinuses.  The flavor seems a lot stickier and more bitter than the aroma, but is also held down by an underlying round sweetness (bready papaya taste) that makes it rich as well instead of just sticky and bone dry.  
The overall effect is one of sweet/tart mouth puckering tropicalia that gives way to pungent hoppy resins and a velvet feel.
Must have again; worth jumping on if you can get your hands on some.  (4.75) 1,459 charactersTheDoctor, Nov 25, 2014
