4.77/5  rDev +4.6%A - Pours a clear, bright dark gold color with a nice, thick, white bubbly lacing ring.
S - Resiny tropical fruit:  red juicy grapefruit, tangerine, mango, papaya, pineapple.  Dank and juicy with little to no malt aroma at all - it's all about the hop blend in this beer.
T - Follows the nose but more balanced on the palate.  Tropical fruit from start to finish without being cloying or sweet, just when the sweetness starts to surface the bitterness beats it down almost immediately without being overbearing and levels out at the end for a lingering sweet & fruity bitterness.  Peppery, spicy tropical fruit goodness: grapefruit rind, oranges, tangerines, mango, some pineapple skins and light to little booziness.
M - Medium body, gentle carbonation on the tongue that subsides to silky, and coats the entire mouth with a mixture of fruit resin and bitterness.
O - Despite the ratings, it really does live up to the score. 930 charactersjzeilinger, Nov 22, 2014
