4.29/5  rDev -5.9%look: 4.25 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.25Big thanks to Threelions for sharing this beer at my little birthday gathering. Poured into a Kate the Great tulip.
A - Poured a hazy orange hue with a one finger white head that leaves light lacing and a nice thin blanket.
S - Aromas of oranges, light malt, faint caramel, very light tropical notes. Not bad, but, not the more aromatic of Lawson's Liquids.
T - Taste is much, much better than the nose. Oranges, faint malts, good light sweetness. Light mango/pineapple notes with loads of hops. Nice tropical notes with some good bitterness and grapefruit peel/pith.
M - Mouthfeel is creamy, lightly carbonated, alcohol hidden very well.
O - Overall, not a bad DIPA. Good tropical notes, alcohol hidden nicely. Pleasant.
