4.77/5  rDev +4.6%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 5This Sip of Sunshine had a bottle date in late August, 2014.  The head on this delicious looking beer is white, dense, and very persistent.  It has been airing out and warming up for the last few minutes and the head is relentless.  The body appears golden/orange, and appears to have a great deal of substance.  
This smells like rich grapefruit/tropical fruit.  This definitely has a rich, bright floral aroma. 
The taste is World Class.  This is the best IPA I have had this year.  I would have to do a side by side to claim this is the best IPA I have ever had.  Layers and layers of flavor abound in this juicy IPA.  Hops/tropical fruit/grapefruit/Honey.  All balanced to create one of Lawson's Finest Liquids.  
The mouthfeel is world-class.  Dense carbonation that coats and flows over your tongue.
Overall - Phenomenal.  One of the top three IPAs I have ever had.
