4.43/5  rDev -2.9%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Served on-tap at The Reservoir in Waterbury, VT.
Lawsons Sip of Sunshine
Ontap reservoir vt
A- Slight hazy golden pour to a snifter. A head rises above one finger with a thick creamy consistency and good retention. A nice ring and islands remain and spots of lace are fixed to the glass with some sheets.
S- Juicy fruits shine in the aroma with no hinting of harshness or bitterness, smooth and fruity. Mangos with tangerine, apricots and citrus juice.
T- Citrus and bitterness open up but the smoothness remains with mango, tangerine complimented by grapefruit and bitter orange zest. Juiciness and tropical stone fruit rules here.
MF- Medium bodied and fairly creamy. Carbonation is high but pretty much on point. Finishes with a moderate bitterness.
The mouthfeel really enhances a juicy stone fruit hop profile. The carbonation isnt aggressive but really pushes those delicate flavors onto the taste buds. 916 characterscbutova, Oct 14, 2014
