4.75/5  rDev +4.2%22oz bomber bottled on 9/18/14. Poured in a snifter glass.
A - Golden hue with a slight haze.  Has a "sunny" shine to it. Hehe.
S -  Very floral with some tropical fruit.  Nice intensity.
T - Lots of nice, bitter floral/resiny /oily hop flavor up front with tropical fruit notes as well. The finish is clean and refreshing.  Almost like a crisp west-coast finish akin to Enjoy By, but a little more graceful.  No noticeable maltiness.
M - Very light for the style.  Incredibly drinkable.  You could drink a couple bombers of this.
O - Really great DIPA.  So flavorful and complex.  I love how much hoppy flavor it packs without inducing a bitter grimace.  Similar to Double Sunshine with the tropical fruit notes, but more oily/floral with a less smooth finish. Overall, a fantastic DIPA. 793 charactersHeadyTheElder, Oct 05, 2014
