4.76/5  rDev +4.4%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.522oz bottle into a Worthy Glass tulip style
A - golden orange appearance...not "cloudy" like some of the other famous Vermont beers from Hill Farmstead and Alchemist. White head good lacing.  
S - Dank pungent tropical  piney oniony fruit bomb.  In your face abrasive smell which I love in my DIPAs. 
T - Follows the nose closely with the expection of bitterness.  Very bitter finish but this is not a bad thing.  This beer packs everything a hop lover would dream of and all of the flavors blend well together.  There are smoother DIPAs out there but very few that are better than this. 
M - strong carbonation, highly dank fruity bitter.  Tastes buds are under assault for minutes after sipping......in a good way.  
O - Reputation of Lawson's beers live up to the hype.  Even better on draft.  Whatever they are doing with hoppy ales  in VT it's working better than anywhere else. 888 charactersHopDeezy, Oct 03, 2014
