5/5  rDev +9.6%From notes
On tap at Prohibition Pig in Waterbury VT
Appearance: It has a nice hazy deep golden/orange color to it. It has a nice thick off-white head that dies down moderately and leaves nice lacing.
Smell: Speechless. The aromas give out hints of loads of tropical fruit (citrus, grapefruit and mango), loads of dank pine resins, and some light buiscuity/caramelly malts. 
Taste: Like the aromas, it has a ton of tropical notes of citrus, grapefruit, mango, even papaya, followed by a great dank piney bitterness and some buiscuity/caramelly malts in the back. 
Mouthfeel: It has a low-med carbonation with a very nice overall balance and feel. 
Drinkability: It's a very smooth drinkable beer accompanied by great flavors and aromas. This beer is so fresh, pungent and dank. This is my first time giving a 5/5 rating but this beer definitely deserves it. The aromatics in this DIPA and that raw in your face bitterness is like none I've ever had. Amazing!
Serving: on tap 982 charactersSebD, Sep 07, 2014
