4.56/5  rDev 0%Bottle received in an IP trade.
Pours a golden hazy yellow, with some darker orange tinges, and a one inch head, with sticky lacing down the glass.
Smells potent, and bright, like the sunshine in the name. Orange, pineapple, grapefruit pith, pine resin.
This one tastes great. It's of course no Double Sunshine, but it's a good facsimile. The malt comes through as a pleasant honey-ish flavor, with tons of juicy fruit flavors- orange, grapefruit, pineapple, lemon, with some grassiness as well, along with some mild piney bitterness. The bitterness is understated and low, letting the bright juicy hop flavors shine brightly.
This one has a medium body, with a light airy and crisp mouthfeel, with a slight, mild lingering bitterness on the palate. Very, very drinkable.
This was great, absolutely delicious. 814 charactersGreesyFizeek, Aug 21, 2014
