4.79/5  rDev +5%look: 5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4.7522 oz bomber poured into Willy glasses and shared in the garage while homebrewing. 
This is a beautiful beer - slightly hazy yellow-orange with a finger of slowly dissipating tight white head. It radiates in the sunshine.
The aroma is amazing - lots of citrus and tropical fruit followed by a bit of spice, resin and dank and just a hint of caramel or butterscotch. 
Taste is also amazing - how do they do this? It starts off sweet and fruity, followed by herbaceous and floral, then ends with a healthy dose of bitterness. A multi-layered experience in a glass.
Mouthfeel is just perfect. Creamy, full and smooth while still refreshing and zingy.
Overall this is just a fabulous beer. I heard it's a bit pricey, but I can't say since I didn't buy it. But I'd have to say the price point would have to be pretty high to exceed its worth. This is damn good! 861 charactersFFreak, Aug 01, 2014
