5/5  rDev +9.6%look: 5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5Had on tap at Prohibition Pig, served in a 13-oz tulip glass
A - Rich golden orange body; not hazy at all. The head was off white, foamy, and quick to dissipate.
S - A divine mix of fruity tangerine, ripe melon, and sappy pine. Just a hint of wildflower honey.
T - A grand slam of hop flavors immediately overwhelms the palate. Just like the nose, except even more intense, and with a tad more grapefruit citrus mixed in with the tangerine. The malt is sweet but not cloying, with the taste of Belgian cookies coming to mind. The finish is not at all bitter, and trails off into a land of hop bliss aftertaste.
M - Velvety with moderate carbonation. For the sweetness, not too viscous. 
O - Damn near perfect. We had Heady Topper and Abner at the table and this was the hands down favorite. I love that it perfectly blends citrus, tropical, pine, and floral hop flavors. I had heard great things about this brewery and, wow, did this brew deliver. 952 charactersporter_collie, Jul 08, 2014
