UPDATE: LAWSONS SIP OF SUNSHINE 4/9/17
Like Lawson's Super Session #2, I have had this a few years ago after it first came out, on draft in a bar/restaurant in Waterbury.  First time out in cans in my state.  Big fan of Double Sunshine and Peril, which are seldom made since Sean Lawson's father died.
Canned 3/21/17, so about three weeks old.
Poured from the 16 oz. can into a Lawson's stemmed tulip.
a: Translucent orange with a finger thick white head which receded to thin surface foam and fairly dense lacing.
s: Intense dank pine resin and citrus.
t: Follows the nose with moderate hop bite over a medium bready malt base.  Dry finish.
m; Medium to full, great body and good carbonation tingle.
o:  Better than I remember and now seems reminiscent of Double Sunshine.  Superlative flavor and Very good to exceptional in all other ways.  Worth seeking out, although at $5+ a can rather pricey, especially given newer competition locally which is about as good.  Changing my ratings: Look from 4.25 to 4, smell from 3.75 to 4.25, taste and overall from 4 to 4.25, feel from 3.75 to 4.5 1,567 charactersscotorum, Apr 21, 2014
